Urges all States that have not already done so to consider ratifying or acceding to the United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime and the Protocols thereto,
United Nations, Treaty Series, vols. 2225, 2237, 2241 and 2326, No. 39574. as well as the United Nations Convention against Corruption,
Ibid., vol. 2349, No. 42146. and encourages States parties that have not yet implemented the conventions to inform the United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime of any impediments that they encounter and of their need for technical assistance to overcome those impediments;
